I need to find P(Y₇ < 27.3), where Y₇ is the 7th order statistic out of 8 observations, and 27.3 is the 70th percentile.

**Key Information:**
- We have 8 observations: Y₁ < Y₂ < ... < Y₈
- The 70th percentile π₀.₇ = 27.3
- This means P(X < 27.3) = 0.70 for a single observation

**Finding P(Y₇ < 27.3):**

The event Y₇ < 27.3 means that the 7th order statistic is less than 27.3. This is equivalent to saying that at least 7 of the 8 observations are less than 27.3.

If we let p = P(X < 27.3) = 0.70, then the number of observations less than 27.3 follows a binomial distribution with n = 8 and p = 0.70.

P(Y₇ < 27.3) = P(at least 7 observations < 27.3)
                = P(exactly 7 observations < 27.3) + P(all 8 observations < 27.3)
                = P(X ≥ 7) where X ~ Binomial(8, 0.70)

Using the binomial formula:
$$P(X = k) = \binom{8}{k}(0.70)^k(0.30)^{8-k}$$

P(X = 7) = $\binom{8}{7}(0.70)^7(0.30)^1$
         = 8 × (0.70)^7 × 0.30
