Input:
Extend Example 1.4-6 to an $n$-sided die. That is, suppose that a fair $n$-sided die is rolled $n$ independent times. A match occurs if side $i$ is observed on the $i$ th trial, $i=1,2, \ldots, n$. Find the limit of this probability as $n$ increases without bound. The unit of the answer should be  .

