= 1 - P(X₁ ≤ 8, X₂ ≤ 8, X₃ ≤ 8)

Since the three drugs are independent:
P(X₁ ≤ 8, X₂ ≤ 8, X₃ ≤ 8) = [P(X ≤ 8)]³

P(X ≤ 8) = 1 - P(X ≥ 9)
= 1 - 0.1493083459
= 0.8506916541

Therefore:
P(max ≥ 9) = 1 - (0.8506916541)³
= 1 - 0.615057
= 0.384943

Let me recalculate more precisely:
(0.8506916541)³ = 0.615057287

P(max ≥ 9) = 1 - 0.615057287 = 0.384942713

Rounding to reasonable significant figures: 0.385

